comment.en: An insulating glass unit (IGU) window only.
A window consisting of two connected single-glass windows.
A window composed of a single glass window connected with an IGU window.
Mounted from the inside, needs to be dismounted from the inside.
Mounted from the outside, needs to be dismounted from the outside.
A set of building elements that contains only the same type of element, e.g. a set of windows with equal properties.
The glass panel that is part of a window.
A window has a frame (lining), and one or more glass panels, and is to be mounted in an opening, predominately in the wall of a building structure.
The frame or lining of a window.
Fair quality, can maybe be reused or refurbished.
Poor quality, cannot be reused, structure should be replaced.
Good quality of the structure, can be reused directly.
